Some said it was because Mrs. Beal wa'n't very well. There was a couple of girls in the family;
bright, lively-lookin' kids that often drove down to the station with their father. Also I'd heard
there was a crippled boy—meningitis or something.

"Now, that's so nice of you! I can see you are one of the people who like to think the very best
of every one right away. Yes, poor Isola—yes I should certainly say she is pretty. Oh, yes;
you might call her that."
